JSON to XML Project

This project is a Python tool that takes a JSON file and converts it into a specific XML format.

How to Build the Project:
Since I only used the standard Python libraries, there is no big build process. I have included a simple script called build.sh to make everything ready. You can run it like this:

    chmod +x build.sh
    ./build.sh

How to Run the Script:
The script needs two things: the JSON file you want to convert and the name of the XML file you want to create. Run it with this command:

    python3 json_to_xml.py <input.json> <output.xml>

For example:
    python3 json_to_xml.py examples/test1.json output.xml

If you don't give exactly two file paths, the script will show you the correct way to use it.

Libraries I used:
I decided to stick with the standard libraries that come with Python so that anyone can run this without installing anything extra.
- json: Used to read the JSON files (https://docs.python.org/3/library/json.html)
- sys: Used to handle the command-line inputs (https://docs.python.org/3/library/sys.html)

Design and Approach:
I used a recursive function for the conversion. JSON is basically a tree of data, so a function that can call itself is the best way to dig through nested objects and arrays. The code checks the type of each item (like if it's a string, number, or list) and then wraps it in the correct XML tag. For "null" values, I made sure it uses the self-closing tag (<null/>) as requested.

Test Files:
I have included a folder called "examples" with some JSON files to test the script:
- examples/test1.json: A basic JSON file with names, numbers, and booleans.
- examples/test2.json: A more complex one with nested arrays and objects to show the recursion works.
